tafsir[9]{c,v,t}:
  55,44,"They will go between it and water that is extremely hot."
  55,48,"These two gardens will have huge fresh branches producing fruit."
  55,50,"In the two gardens there will be two springs flowing between them with water."
  55,52,"In them there will be two types of every fruit to enjoy."
  55,58,"As though they are rubies and coral in their beauty and purity."
  55,60,"The reward of those who properly followed their Lord is only that Allah will give them a proper recompense."
  55,62,"Below those two mentioned gardens are another two gardens."
  55,64,"Both of the deepest green."
  55,66,"In these two gardens there are springs that forcefully gush forth with water. The gushing of their water does not stop."